CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1959, pg. 2, reads: "Paid Own Workers - Joe Watts and two of his four workers, Dorothy Parnell and Shirley Oliver, compare notes during a lull in Tuesday's elections. Watts, duly elected Democratic committeeman in 13th Ward's Sixth District, had to pay his own workers because Ward Chairman Sarah Kirk refused to recognize him as a district official.  Linn Washington and Henry Ryan Helped with the finances."
TitMainTitle: Dorothy Parnell, Joe Watts, and Shirley Oliver wearing Democratic campaign signs and standing in front of car
